    "summary": "Yes, two notes -- brief at line 17, deeper at line 25",
    "content": "Yes, two notes. Brief reasoning:\n\nAt line 17, the author already provides a gloss -- 境界（界限）. The author is telling the reader \"by 境界 I mean limits/bounds.\" A brief TN here simply adds the etymological layer: \"境界 = the bounds (界) of a *jing* (境).\" This costs the reader one parenthetical and plants a seed.\n\nIf we wait until line 25, the reader has already encountered 境界 twice (lines 17 and 19) without knowing it contains 境. When the deeper note at line 25 reveals the connection, the reader has to retroactively reparse two passages. That is unnecessary cognitive friction.\n\nThe two-note structure mirrors how the author teaches concepts throughout the collection -- light touch first, full revelation later. The line 17 note is the primer; the line 25 note is the payoff."
